description:
China's Wild West - On the Wild Yak Trek | Nature Documentary

Watch 'Magical Moors - A Mysterious World Full of Life' here:  https://youtu.be/LxYT7QMT_pA

The cold and dry steppe of China’s wild west is a remote, inaccessible and inhospitable area and it is the home of the last wild Yak, the wild cattle species resisting 6000 metres altitude. For the first time a camera crew was allowed to watch the beauty, intelligence and brutal power of this enormous species and they faced an attack of a wild Yak bull. Yet the species is endangered and that is the next challenge for rapidly developing China. Because the wild Yak is very important for China’s future.
